         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">27th Oct. 1853. ¶  ¶ In reply to your letter of the 19th ultimo ¶  I do myself the honor to inform you that the sum of £100:0:0 is available and will be at once placed at your service to cover the exp...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">53.10.27</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">From Lewis Gilles</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">No. 53/679, unit 1, p. 258, VPRS 3150 outward letter books to miscellaneous and Assay Master, VA 856 Chief Secretary's Office, Public Record Office, Victoria.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">27th Oct. 1853.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>In reply to your letter of the 19th ultimo<note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">See M to C. La Trobe, 19 September 1853.</p>
               </note> I do myself the honor to inform you that the sum of £100:0:0 is available and will be at once placed at your service to cover the expense of your outfit</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>2 I am further directed to inform you that H. E. considers it might be advisable for you to visit the Grampian Range, and country to the northward in the course of the Spring but at the same time the L. G. leaves you to take your own choice of the District wherein to prosecute your researches.</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">By order.</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>L. Gilles.</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>A. C. S.<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Assistant Colonial Secretary.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">The Government Botanist</p>
